children.subject: I have to submit a 4 year course plan somewhere, so it's definitely tentative; however I think I might want to start thinking of the math/stat courses I want to take next semester.

189 will go easier if you take 126 before it instead of concurrently. Also, I wouldn't treat 182 being offered in the fall as a certainty. It's tentatively listed for next semester, but there's a good chance it doesn't end up offered
Research >>> classes. If you can do 12-15 hrs of research with this workload it's fine, otherwise aggressively drop classes in favor of doing research.

Math104 isn't needed for the classes listed, it's only needed for grad classes, so the timing of that is flexible depending on when you take grad classes. 

135 is easier than 104, so you can swap the two if you want a lighter fall, but if you can handle the current load you can probably handle the fall (its a nice mix of linear algebra, coding, and analysis)

I have yet to take cs 189 but looking at the topics listed here: https://www.eecs189.org/syllabus/, it may be helpful to take 135 before 189 to give you a glipse of them or stat 151A (instead of 135). Also taking 126 before 189 would be a nice.

history.content:
Schedule for this semester: CS170, CS188, Math 110, lighter research, sort of on the lighter side but wasn't feeling good this semester for reasons, was in 126 instead of 188 before and instead am taking 188.

Just trying to plan out classes with respect to ML/AI path/grad school 

Fall 2020: EE127, CS161, Math 104, research (BAIR potentially)

Spring 2021: CS189, EE126, Stat 135, research

(EDIT)

Fall 2021: <strikethrough> CS182 </strikethrough, CS162, Math 128A

Spring 2022: Grad classes

Should I switch 135 to before 104 (how hard is the jump from my spring semester to my fall 2020 semester as currently written?)? Should I take grad classes in fall semester instead of spring and maybe move 162 to spring 2022? I'll also look at what grad classes are most recommended (and update this post). another way I was potentially thinking of doing is is 135 fall 2020, 128A spring 2021, math 104 fall 2021, but I feel like math 104 should be taken asap?? <- although this is actually easier for me workload wise, in case I move to BAIR junior year
